#### Shinysender Loader ####
## Shinysender Loader Version 0.0.3
## Staging version
## This sets the cache dir, but does not turn Packrat on to
## rehydrate the packages.
## We need to do this, so that devtools() is available, which is
## needed to download private Github repos.  We also need to
## explictly load devtools(), otherwise the GITHUB_PAT environment
## variable doesn't reach the downloader (Not sure why this is
## the case)

# .Rprofile code to use user's packrat cache
# (to avoid recompiling packages for each app)
# and to enable Packrat on startup

Sys.setenv(R_PACKRAT_CACHE_DIR = "~/R/packratcache")
Sys.setenv(MAKEFLAGS="-j2")
packrat::set_opts(use.cache=TRUE)
# We *have* to explicitly load devtools otherwise it doesn't
# pick up GITHUB_PAT.
library(devtools)

#### Shinysender Loader End ####
